: 17, "name": "France", "slug": "france"}], "biography": "Pierre Schoendoerffer (French: Pierre Schœndœrffer; 5 May 1928 – 14 March 2012) was a French film director, a screenwriter, a writer, a war reporter, a war cameraman, a renowned First Indochina War veteran, a cinema academician. He was president of the Académie des Beaux-Arts for 2001 and for 2007.In 1967, he was the winner of the Academy Award for Best Documentary Feature for The Anderson Platoon. The film followed a platoon of American soldiers for six weeks at the height of fighting in Vietnam during 1966. Source: Wikidata; 01/08/2023", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2025-05-22T22:41:00.345981+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 4927, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pierre_Schoendoerffer"}], "uuid": "9b2514d2-a20a-4bfb-99dd-6ef8982ea705", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "31050", "external_references": [{"id": 25438, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q742622"}, {"id": 30918, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "71397543"}, {"id": 30919, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n92070383"}, {"id": 30920, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n92070383"}], "date_modified": "2025-05-22T22:41:00.346320+10:00"}, {"id": 83015, "name": "Chris Marke", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 3104449, "title": "Ak: Akira Kurosawa", "work_id": 115918, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-05-09T11:54:33.842396+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "2f7741e1-46ac-46de-b021-973b0a8fd0d9", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "31369", "external_references": [{"id": 39248, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q121078769"}], "date_modified": "2025-05-22T22:40:59.449429+10:00"}, {"id": 83014, "name": "Andre Cayatte", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 3104441, "title": "Le Miroir a Deux Faces = the Mirror Has Two Faces", "work_id": 115915, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 3104989, "title": "Le Passage du Rhin = Tomorrow Is My Turn", "work_id": 116191, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "Marcel Truc", "date_of_birth": "1909-02-03", "date_of_death": "1989-02-06", "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [{"id": 4, "name": "French", "slug": "french"}], "places_of_operation": [{"id": 17, "name": "France", "slug": "france"}], "biography": "André Cayatte (3 February 1909, in Carcassonne – 6 February 1989, in Paris) was a French filmmaker, writer and lawyer, who became known for his films centering on themes of crime, justice, and moral responsibility.\nCayatte began his directoral career at the German-controlled Continental Films during the French occupation.  Some of Cayatte's earlier films that addressed his characteristic themes include Justice est faite (Justice is Done; 1950), Nous sommes tous des assassins (We Are All Murderers; 1952), and Le passage du Rhin (Tomorrow Is My Turn; 1960).\nIn 1963, he undertook a bold experiment in film narrative with a set of two films: Jean-Marc ou La vie conjugale (Anatomy of a Marriage: My Days with Jean-Marc) and Françoise ou La vie conjugale (Anatomy of a Marriage: My Days with Françoise). These two films tell the same story from two different points of view. His 1973 film, Il n'y a pas de fumée sans feu, won the Silver Bear Special Jury Prize at the 23rd Berlin International Film Festival.\n\n", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-08-15T10:24:18.164553+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 1630, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andr%C3%A9_Cayatte"}], "uuid": "8bc73512-9cb3-4a38-981c-363a57547389", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "31047", "external_references": [{"id": 7124, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q517725"}, {"id": 7125, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "73851103"}, {"id": 7126, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n82102988"}, {"id": 7127, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n82102988"}], "date_modified": "2025-05-22T22:55:10.206412+10:00"}]}